@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>



<head>

    <title>Privacy Policy</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

    <p>This is the privacy policy for [Your Website/Application Name]. It outlines the types of personal information we collect, how we use and protect that information, and your rights regarding your personal data.</p>

    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>[Describe the types of information you collect from users, such as name, email address, contact information, etc.]</p>

    <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>[Explain how you use the collected information, such as to provide services, personalize user experience, communicate with users, etc.]</p>

    <h2>Information Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
    <p>[Specify if and how you share user information with third parties, such as service providers, business partners, etc.]</p>

    <h2>Data Security</h2>
    <p>[Describe the security measures you have in place to protect user data from unauthorized access or misuse.]</p>

    <h2>Cookies</h2>
    <p>[Explain the use of cookies on your website/application, including the types of cookies used, their purpose, and how users can manage or disable them.]</p>

    <h2>Third-Party Links</h2>
    <p>[If applicable, mention any third-party links or services on your website/application and clarify that your privacy policy does not cover those external sites/services.]</p>

    <h2>Your Rights</h2>
    <p>[Inform users about their rights regarding their personal data, such as the right to access, modify, or delete their information.]</p>

    <h2>Contact Us</h2>
    <p>[Provide contact information for users to reach out to you with privacy-related inquiries or concerns.]</p>

    <p>This privacy policy was last updated on [Date].</p>
</body>


